title: Lawmakers see rise in threatening messages as TikTok users swarm Congress
description: After TikTok urged users to call their representatives in protest of a potential ban, U.S. Capitol Police are investigating menacing calls as users swarm Congress.

title: United Nations adopts U.S.-led resolution to safely develop AI
description: The United Nations AI agreement, which had the support of U.S. tech adversaries including Russia and China, seeks to promote human rights.

title: Intel CEO says Biden wants chip factories ‘bigger’ and 'sooner’
description: Intel CEO Pat Gelsinger said President Biden is pushing him to get new federally-funded chip factories up and running faster, amid reports of delays and creeping costs in Washington’s flagship initiative to revitalize U.S. high-tech manufacturing.

title: Why is the government suing Apple? Look at your iPhone’s restrictions.
description: These things you can’t do with your iPhone are the heart of allegations that Apple is an illegal monopoly.

title: Justice Department, states accuse Apple of holding a smartphone monopoly
description: The Justice Department accused Apple of breaking federal antitrust law, plunging the tech giant into a high-stakes showdown over its alleged abuse of power.

title: Trump Media, launched after an insurrection, faces rebellion of its own
description: Three men with pivotal roles in founding Donald Trump’s firm and its proposed merger partner, Digital World Acquisition, are in court battles with the companies.

title: Reddit goes public today. Users are wary of what comes next.
description: There’s nothing online quite like Reddit. Will an IPO change that?
